## Original Reference

The original repository accompanies:

Leonardo Fierro, "Adaptive Loudness Compensation in Music Listening", SMC 2019.

Paper link:
http://smc2019.uma.es/articles/S2/S2_01_SMC2019_paper.pdf

## Status

This is an active restoration and modernization effort. The MATLAB code is retained as provenance, while the Python code is intended to become the maintainable implementation going forward.

## Validation Notes

The current test suite checks:

- contour generation shape and a 1 kHz ISO 226 reference point
- compensation trace consistency when mastering and listening levels match
- overlap-add reconstruction
- shelf filter coefficient generation
- end-to-end processing on a synthetic WAV file
- WAV export and import round-trip behavior
